comments:
In 1889 the part of the parish of Bedminster in Bristol County 
    Borough became part of Gloucestershire, in 1894 the remaining part of the parish in 
    Somerset became the separate parish of Bedminster Without, so that thereafter 
    Bedminster was wholly in Gloucestershire. Abolished 30.9.1896 and added to the 
    parish of South Bristol.
Abolished 25.3.1885 and added to the parish of Brockley.
